      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>Schedule G, Part III, Lines 1-8</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>The District 45 gaming activities consist of ONE TIME RAFFLES that were held though out the year. We hold some raffles that are open to members only, and some raffles that include the public. Our biggest raffle is the "LCIF Super Raffle" with an income of $17,030 - All non-cash prizes for the LCIF Super Raffle are donated, all proceeds from the LICF Super Raffle, after expenses, are donated to the non-profit 501(c)(3) Lions Club International Foundation. Line 3 - In addition to the cash prizes, there are approximately $3,000 worth of non-cash prizes given away during the LCIF Super Faffle - all of the non-cash prizes were donated</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
